Warm-up Sketch — Day 2. The Stinky King. 
But he’s not stinky in a smelly old man kind of way. He’s stinky in like a… nepo-baby, tax the poor, wear slippers around the castle, hang the jester(s), farts into his throne pillow, munches on cherry tomatoes in close-up shots… kind of way.

Let us not forget the lady knight that started it all. You know her name… *drum roll*… The one… *a surge of energy through the crowd*… THE ONLY… *pyrotechnics engage* *members of the audience start frothing at the mouth* …YOUR QUEEN… *a single tears runs down an elders cheek*… BE—UH—TRICE!!! *fireworks fly freely* *crowd goes absolutely ballistic* *deafening applause* *it lasts for days* *cut back to the elder who is openly weeping* *I do a backflip* *the crowd somehow goes even wilder* *it lasts for weeks*

Had fun with this piece. Wanted to practice framing for a manga/graphic novel since I don’t have much experience with it. It’s surprisingly difficult to measure anatomy and proportions when you’re not seeing the full body. Luckily, Beatrice’s armor does a lot of the heavy lifting, no pun intended. 🤭(this emoji represents me going “tee hee”)
